\begin_layout Standard
Let's assume that consumers we simply maximising overall assets subject
 to needs and would eventually come to an equilibrium.
 We know that consumer can't always come to a richer place with higher income
 - as places are limited - but they can remain in some place always.
 There is thus always a place for everybody in the economy.
 We're not using a discrete model.
 
\end_layout

